    "recap_url": "https://www.fausports.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-owls-rally-in-extra-innings-to-stun-umbc",
    "recap_headline": "Florida Atlantic University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BOCA RATON, Fla. \u00a0\u2013\nJohn Martinez\ndelivered a walk-off, two-RBI single in the bottom of the 11th inning to help Florida Atlantic baseball stun UMBC 10-9 on Friday night at the FAU Baseball Stadium. The Owls (12-6) have won six in a row and will look to clinch the series against the Retrievers (6-7) on Saturday at noon.\nTHE BEGINNING\nA\nMichael Perazza\nsacrifice fly opened the scoring in the first inning, and\nJayden Harriel\ndoubled the lead in the second with his first career home run to make it 2-0. The teams traded the lead back and forth from that point forward. UMBC went ahead 3-2 in the third before the Owls tied it in the fourth and regained the lead 4-3 in the fifth.\nTHE TURNING POINT\nUMBC scored one in each of the sixth, seventh, and eighth innings to lead 6-4. The Owls went into the bottom of the ninth, needing two to extend the game. After a leadoff walk, back-to-back fielder's choice groundouts had the home side down to its final out. Perazza was the Owls' last hope. Facing a 1-2 count, the redshirt sophomore got just the pitch he was looking for and launched a no-doubter over the wall in right centerfield to tie the game and send it to extra innings.\nTHE FINISH\nAfter a scoreless 10th, UMBC went back in front with a bases-loaded, three-RBI double from catcher Derek Paris. Now trailing 9-6, the Owls would once again need to rally in the bottom of the inning.\nWard lined a one-out single off the glove of the UMBC third baseman to spark the rally again. The Owls then drew three straight two-out walks to force home a run. With the bases still loaded,\nMarshall Lipsey\nwas hit by a pitch to force in another run. Suddenly, it was 9-8, and the game-winning run was in scoring position. This time, Martinez was the last hope. Down 1-2 in the count, the Owls' second baseman lined a single to left field. Perazza scored the tying run, and\nBrando Leroux\nfollowed close behind, sliding headfirst into home for the walk-off.\nQUOTABLE\nHead Coach\nJohn McCormack\nPostgame with\n@FAUCoachMac\n#WIP\n\ud83c\udfdd\ufe0f\npic.twitter.com/uaEmVUX0tO\n\u2014 Florida Atlantic Baseball (@FAUBaseball)\nMarch 14, 2026\nTHE BATS\nThe Owls finished with nine hits, led by two each by Martinez, Perazza,\nNick Romano\n, and\nIan Collier\n.\nMartinez's game-winning hit extended his team-lead in RBI to 14.\nCollier also doubled and drove in a run.\nRomano reached base four times with two singles and two walks.\nTHE ARMS\nJames Litman\nstarted and completed 5.1 innings. He allowed four runs on seven hits.\nZach Kilby\npitched 2.2 innings and struck out four. He allowed two runs, one of which was earned.\nBrayden Gilson\ncompleted a scoreless ninth.\nKyzer Smith\nheld the Retrievers in check in the 10th before being tagged for all three runs in the 11th.\nBryan Boully\nrelieved Smith and recorded the last out in the 11th. The fifth-year senior was credited with the win.\nWHAT'S NEXT\nGame two has been moved up to a noon start on Saturday to avoid potential weather later in the day.\nFOLLOW THE OWLS\nTo stay up to date on all things Florida Atlantic baseball, follow us on social media @faubaseball."
  },
